Nightmare Mudlib 3.2 SimulEfun: save_database()

int save_database(string file, mapping data);

DESCRIPTION
You pass to this argument the name of a database file which you want written to and a mapping data,
it will attempt to serilize all values using save_variable for proper restoring.

Note any function pointers will be set to 0.

LOCATION
/adm/simul_efun/read_database.c

SEE ALSO
save_database(), load_database(), log_file(), read_file(), write_file()
